olive oil
2 clove garlic
½ onion
½ head cos lettuce
1 pear
½ carrot
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet pork mince
½ packet kecap manis
1 tbs soy sauce
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
½ Fresh Chilli
1 sachet Crispy Shallots

Finely grate the garlic. Finely chop the brown
onion (see ingredients). Shred the cos lettuce (see
ingredients). Thinly slice the pear. Grate the carrot
(see ingredients).

In a small bowl, add the garlic aioli and season
with salt and pepper. Set aside.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over a medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add
the onion and carrot, season with salt and cook,
stirring, until softened slightly, 4-5 minutes. Add
the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

Increase the heat to high, then add the pork mince
and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until just
browned, 3-4 minutes. Remove the pan from the
heat, then add the kecap manis (see ingredients)
and soy sauce and stir until just combined,
1 minute. Season to taste.

Microwave the mini flour tortillas on a plate in
10 second bursts until warmed through.

Thinly slice the long green chilli (if using). Bring
everything to the table to serve. Spread a thin layer
of the aioli over a tortilla. Top with a helping of
cos lettuce, some pear and Vietnamese-style pork.
Sprinkle with the crispy shallots and chilli.